message.content: cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE. The paper presents a question answering system over DBpedia, which is a structured knowledge base. The system focuses on solving non-aggregation questions and proposes a graph traversal method to comprehend natural language queries and provide accurate answers. The paper involves natural language processing, information retrieval, and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with the arXiv CS sub-categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
